ec_single: Inclusion: Any woman 18-58 years of age
Inclusion: Secondary amenorrhea defined by either menstrual cycle interval persistently exceeding 45 days and/or those with period loss for 3 months or more
Exclusion: Women who never had periods (primary amenorrhea).
Inclusion: Female, age 14-25 years, skeletally mature with bone age ≥ 14 years (only 2% of growth left)

Inclusion: For women of reproductive age, agree to use an effective non-hormonal contraceptive method or a progestin releasing intrauterine device (no evidence of systemic skeletal effects) for the study duration
Inclusion: Negative βHCG (pregnancy test)
Inclusion: TSH, prolactin, potassium, magnesium within the normal range
Inclusion: Serum ALT ≤ 3 times upper limit of normal, LDL ≤ 190 mg/dl
Inclusion: eGFR ≥ 30ml/minute
Inclusion: Less than 3 menses in the preceding 6 months
Inclusion: BMD Z-score \< -1.0 at ≥ 1 skeletal site
Inclusion: Dental check-up within the past year
Exclusion: Disease other than FHA known to affect bone, including untreated thyroid dysfunction, Cushing's disease, renal failure, diabetes mellitus
Exclusion: Use of bisphosphonates
Exclusion: Use of other medications known to affect bone metabolism within 3 months of the study (other than calcium and vitamin D supplementation).
Exclusion: Substance abuse disorder; current smoker
Exclusion: History of malignancy or Paget disease of bone
Exclusion: Pregnant, planning to become pregnant within 12 months after the end of treatment and/or breastfeeding
Exclusion: Cardiovascular: Myocardial infarction or stroke; history of hypertension or use of anti-hypertensive medications
Exclusion: Immunodeficiency or taking immunosuppressive therapy
Exclusion: Other conditions that can cause oligo-amenorrhea such as PCOS, premature ovarian insufficiency

Exclusion: Dental: Osteonecrosis of the jaw (ONJ) or risk factor for ONJ, such as invasive dental procedures (tooth extraction, dental implants, oral surgery in the past 3 months), poor oral hygiene, periodontal and/or pre-existing dental disease, and current use of corticosteroids
Exclusion: Planned invasive dental procedure over the next 12 months (the duration of the study)

Exclusion: Known sensitivity or absolute contraindication to any of the products or components of the medications to be administered (romosozumab, zoledronic acid, transdermal estradiol, micronized progesterone, calcium or vitamin D supplements)
Exclusion: BMD Z-score \<-2.5 (who we will refer for evaluation)

Inclusion: Inclusion criteria for participation are a gynecological age (age since menarche) \> 5 and \< 25 years, and chronological age \> 18 years, within 90-110% of ideal body weight as determined by the 1983 Metropolitan height and weight table for women, and exercise \< 10 h/wk and run \< 10 mi/wk, day-awake/night-asleep schedule.
Inclusion: Women in the FHA and PCOS groups have to fulfill the diagnostic criteria of FHA or PCOS and to have all other causes of amenorrhea and anovulation excluded.

Exclusion: Exclusion criteria are smoking, medications, including psychotropic or illicit drugs, medical, neurological, or ophthalmologic disease except acuity problems, a weight loss or gain of \> 10 lb within a year preceding or since the onset of amenorrhea, a major Axis I disorder other than depression, parturition in the last 12 months and/or lactating in the last 6 months.
Inclusion: Male and female patients, aged 18 and above.
Inclusion: ApoA-I \< 70 mg/dL
Inclusion: Symptomatic or asymptomatic cardiovascular disease
Inclusion: Diagnosis of genetically confirmed HDL-c deficiency due to defects in genes coding for ABCA1 and/or ApoA-1
Inclusion: Stable doses of lipid lowering therapies for at least 6 weeks prior to baseline procedures
Exclusion: Females of childbearing potential
Exclusion: Patients with LCAT mutations
Exclusion: Patients who experienced recent cardiovascular or cerebrovascular events
Exclusion: Hypertriglyceridemia (\>500 mg/dL)
Exclusion: Severe anemia (Hgb \< 10 g/dL)
Exclusion: Uncontrolled diabetes (HbA1c \>10%)
Exclusion: Congestive heart failure (NYHA class II or higher)
Exclusion: Contraindication for MRI scanning (e.g., implanted metal objects, claustrophobia)
Inclusion: healthy subject
Inclusion: 14-15 years old
Inclusion: eligible for their school-leaving booster for DTP

Inclusion: received a complete primary vaccination with a 5-component acellular pertussis vaccine (DT5aP-IPV-Hib) at 3, 5 and 12 months of age and vaccinated with a 5-component acellular pertussis vaccine (Td5aP-IPV or Td5aP + IPV) as a booster at 5½ years of age
Inclusion: informed consent form signed by the subject and parent(s)/legal representative
Inclusion: subject understand and comply with the study procedures (i.e. able to read and write Swedish)

Inclusion: female must provide an agreement that they are either sexually continent or practice adequate contraceptive methods (intra-uterine contraceptive device (IUCD), hormonal contraceptives, condoms or other adequate barrier contraception).
Exclusion: acute febrile illness or axillary temperature ≥38.0°C at the time of vaccination

Exclusion: receipt of immunoglobulin within the previous 3 months, immunosuppression (e g evidence of impaired cell mediated immunity, receipt of immunosuppressant drugs within the previous 3 months or receipt of systemic corticosteroids given daily or on alternate days at ≥20 mg/day prednisone equivalent during \>14 days within the past 30 days)
Exclusion: receipt of a non-study vaccine in the past 30 days
Exclusion: evolving encephalopathy not attributable to another identifiable cause within 7 days of administration of a previous dose of any vaccine
Exclusion: booster vaccination with tetanus, low dose diphtheria and acellular pertussis vaccine since the booster vaccination at 5½ years of age
Exclusion: previous clinical or bacteriological diagnosis of diphtheria, tetanus or pertussis
Exclusion: hypersensitivity to any component of any of the study vaccines
Exclusion: current participation in any other clinical trial or participation in any clinical trial in the previous month
Exclusion: inability to adhere to the protocol, including plans to move from the area
Exclusion: severe chronic disease
Exclusion: family history of congenital or hereditary immunodeficiency
Exclusion: any sever thrombocytopenia or any other coagulation disorder that would contraindicate intramuscular injection
Exclusion: any medical condition, which in the opinion of the investigator, might interfere with the evaluation of the study objectives.
